16 "8-3-224.
17 (a) As used in this Code section:
18 (1) 'Artificial intelligence' means a machine based system that can, for a given set of
19 human defined objectives, make predictions, recommendations, or decisions influencing
20 a real or virtual environment.
21 (2) 'Automated decision tool' means a system or service that uses artificial intelligence
22 and has been specifically developed and marketed or specifically modified to make, or
23 to be a controlling factor in making, consequential decisions.
24 (3) 'Judicatory' means any court, official, board, tribunal, commission, municipal or
25 county authority, council, or similar body exercising judicial or quasi-judicial powers
26 authorized by law, as well as any arbitrator, administrative law judge, mediator, or similar
27 adjudicator authorized by law to act on behalf or at the request of any public official or
28 body.
29 (b) Any prohibition in this article against any discriminatory housing practice shall include
30 a prohibition against such discriminatory housing practice resulting from the use of or
31 reliance upon artificial intelligence or automated decision tools.
32 (c) In any action or proceeding before any judicatory stemming from a prohibition on
33 discriminatory housing practices, reliance upon artificial intelligence or automated decision
34 tools shall not be a defense to an allegation of discrimination.
35 (d) No person shall use artificial intelligence or automated decision tools to make
36 determinations relating to the sale, rental, or financing of dwellings or in the provision of
37 brokerage services or facilities in connection with the sale or rental of a dwelling, without
38 the participation or review of such determinations by an individual responsible for making
39 such determination.
40 (e) No person shall use artificial intelligence or automated decision tools to make
41 determinations relating to the sale, rental, or financing of dwellings or in the provision of
