42 brokerage services or facilities in connection with the sale or rental of a dwelling, without
43 disclosing to any affected individuals that such tools were used.
44 (f)(1) If the Attorney General determines, after notice and hearing, that a person has
45 violated either subsection (c) or (d) of this Code section, the Attorney General may issue
46 an administrative order imposing a penalty of not more than $10,000.00.
47 (2) The hearing and any administrative review pursuant to this subsection shall be
48 conducted in accordance with the procedure for contested cases under Chapter 13 of Title
49 50, the 'Georgia Administrative Procedure Act.' Any person who has exhausted all
50 administrative remedies available and who is aggrieved or adversely affected by a final
51 order or action of the Attorney General shall have the right of judicial review in
52 accordance with Chapter 13 of Title 50, the 'Georgia Administrative Procedure Act.'"
53 SECTION 3.
54 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
